The paper discusses the use of answer set programming (ASP) for declaratively representing and solving hard problems, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses transformations of logic programs, which falls under the category of logic in computer science (cs.LO) and programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also mentions the integration of separate programs, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper discusses the problem-solving capacity of disjunctive logic programs, which falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
